snippet.textDisplay: Beautiful words, beautiful message, sung by the best of the voices.. What is not to like? Coke studio, you have outdone yourself.. I had learnt the Pakistani national anthem when I was growing up in India and had started to learn Urdu.. Fell in love with it the day I heard it first.. Been a long time in Canada now and this is where I learnt how amazing people are on both sides of the border.. If we overlook media and politics; we are basically two brothers born to the same mother, who went separate ways to do their thing.. No matter what, we are still family.. I wish one day all that exists between the two nations is peace and love..
